HR:

H2:<div id="intro">Introduction</div>
P:<a href="/pages/documentation.html">BAX is a modern, lightweight, and SEO-friendly static site generator built with pure Batch and Bash scripts. No dependencies, no bloat - just pure static site magic!</a>
P:BAX stands for Batch and Axcora X, combining the power of Windows Batch and Linux Bash to create a cross-platform static site generator.

H2:<div id="install">Installation</div>

H3:Clone the Repository
CODE:git clone https://github.com/mesinkasir/bax.git
CODE:cd bax

H3:Project Structure
CODE:bax/
CODE:├── bax.bat            # Windows build script
CODE:├── bax.sh             # Linux/Mac build script
CODE:├── run.bat            # Windows dev mode script
CODE:├── run.sh             # Linux/Mac dev mode script
CODE:├── config.zet         # Site configuration
CODE:├── style.css          # Custom styles
CODE:├── data/              # Blog posts
CODE:│   └── *.zet
CODE:├── pages/             # Static pages
CODE:│   └── *.zet
CODE:└── public/            # Generated output (auto-created)
CODE:    ├── index.html
CODE:    ├── pages/
CODE:    ├── tags/
CODE:    └── *.html

HR:

H2:<div id="config">Configuration</div>

H3:Create config.zet
P:Create a file named config.zet in your project root with the following structure:

CODE:SITE_TITLE:My Awesome Site
CODE:SITE_URL:https://myawesome.site
CODE:SITE_DESCRIPTION:My awesome static site
CODE:SITE_IMAGE:https://myawesome.site/og-image.jpg
CODE:SITE_FAVICON:/favicon.ico
CODE:POSTS_PER_PAGE:6

H3:Navigation
P:Add navigation menu items in config.zet:

CODE:NAV:
CODE:  - text: Home
CODE:    url: /
CODE:  - text: About
CODE:    url: /about
CODE:  - text: Portfolio
CODE:    url: /portfolio
CODE:  - text: Contact
CODE:    url: /contact

H3:Configuration Options
TABLE:
THEAD:
TR:TH:Option,TH:Description,TH:Required
/THEAD:
TBODY:
TR:TD:SITE_TITLE,TD:Site title for navbar and SEO,TD:Yes
TR:TD:SITE_URL,TD:Site URL with or without trailing slash,TD:Yes
TR:TD:SITE_DESCRIPTION,TD:Site description for SEO,TD:No
TR:TD:SITE_IMAGE,TD:Default OG image for social sharing,TD:No
TR:TD:SITE_FAVICON,TD:Path to favicon,TD:No
TR:TD:POSTS_PER_PAGE,TD:Number of posts per page,TD:No (default: 6)
TR:TD:NAV,TD:Navigation menu items,TD:No
/TBODY:
/TABLE:

HR:

H2:<div id="content">Content Creation</div>

H3:Creating Blog Posts
P:Create .zet files in the data/ folder. Each file becomes a blog post.

CODE:TITLE:My First Blog Post
CODE:DATE:15 July 2026
CODE:IMG:https://example.com/image.jpg
CODE:DESC:This is my first blog post
CODE:TAGS:technology programming tutorial
CODE:
CODE:H2:Introduction
CODE:P:Welcome to my blog!
CODE:
CODE:H3:Sub Section
CODE:P:This is a sub section.
CODE:
CODE:UL:
CODE:LI:Item one
CODE:LI:Item two
CODE:/UL:
CODE:
CODE:TAGS:technology programming

H3:Supported Content Types
TABLE:
THEAD:
TR:TH:Tag,TH:Description,TH:Example
/THEAD:
TBODY:
TR:TD:TITLE,TD:Post title,TD:TITLE:My Post
TR:TD:DATE,TD:Publication date,TD:DATE:15 July 2026
TR:TD:IMG,TD:Featured image URL,TD:IMG:https://example.com/image.jpg
TR:TD:DESC,TD:Post description,TD:DESC:My description
TR:TD:TAGS,TD:Space-separated tags,TD:TAGS:tech programming
TR:TD:H2-H6,TD:Headings,TD:H2:Section Title
TR:TD:P,TD:Paragraph,TD:P:My paragraph text
TR:TD:UL/OL,TD:Lists,TD:UL: / /UL:
TR:TD:LI,TD:List item,TD:LI:Item
TR:TD:CODE,TD:Code block,TD:CODE:console.log('Hello')
TR:TD:TABLE,TD:HTML table,TD:TABLE: / /TABLE:
TR:TD:BLOCKQUOTE,TD:Blockquote,TD:BLOCKQUOTE:Quote text
TR:TD:HR,TD:Horizontal rule,TD:HR:
/TBODY:
/TABLE:

H3:Creating Static Pages
P:Create .zet files in the pages/ folder for static pages like About, Contact, etc.

CODE:TITLE:About Me
CODE:DESC:Learn more about me
CODE:IMG:https://example.com/about.jpg
CODE:
CODE:H1:About Me
CODE:P:Welcome to my about page.
CODE:
CODE:H2:My Story
CODE:P:I am a web developer...

H3:URL Field
P:You can add a custom URL field in pages:

CODE:TITLE:About Me
CODE:URL:https://mywebsite.com/about

HR:

H2:<div id="build">Build Commands</div>

H3:Windows
CODE:bax.bat

H3:Linux / macOS
CODE:chmod +x bax.sh
CODE:./bax.sh

H3:Clean Build
P:To clean and rebuild:

CODE:# Windows
CODE:rmdir /s /q public
CODE:bax.bat
CODE:
CODE:# Linux/macOS
CODE:rm -rf public
CODE:./bax.sh

H3:Build Output
P:After build, all generated files will be in the public/ folder.

HR:

H2:<div id="dev">Run Dev Mode</div>
P:After building, run the development server to preview your site:

H3:Windows
CODE:run.bat

H3:Linux / macOS
CODE:./run.sh

P:This will start a local server at http://127.0.0.1:3000.

HR:

H2:<div id="deploy">Deployment</div>

H3:GitHub Pages
P:BAX includes a ready-to-use <a href="/pages/documentation.html">GitHub Actions workflow</a>.

CODE:# Rename workflow file
CODE:mv .github/workflows/deploy.yml.example .github/workflows/deploy.yml
CODE:
CODE:# Push to GitHub
CODE:git add .
CODE:git commit -m "Deploy BAX site"
CODE:git push origin main

P:Then enable GitHub Pages in your repository settings.

H3:Netlify
UL:
LI:Build command: ./bax.sh
LI:Publish directory: public/
/UL:

H3:Vercel
UL:
LI:Build command: ./bax.sh
LI:Output directory: public/
/UL:

H3:Cloudflare Pages
UL:
LI:Build command: ./bax.sh
LI:Build output: public/
/UL:

HR:

H2:<div id="seo">SEO Features</div>

H3:Auto-Generated Meta Tags
P:BAX automatically generates <a href="/pages/documentation.html">SEO-friendly meta tags</a>:

UL:
LI:Title tag
LI:Description meta
LI:Open Graph tags (Facebook, LinkedIn)
LI:Twitter Card tags (Twitter)
LI:Generator meta
/UL:

H3:Sitemap & Robots
P:BAX automatically generates:
UL:
LI:sitemap.xml - for search engines
LI:robots.txt - for crawler instructions
/UL:

H3:Priority System
P:BAX uses a priority system for SEO metadata:
OL:
LI:Post/Page specific (highest priority)
LI:Site-wide config (fallback)
LI:Default values (last resort)
/OL:

HR:

H2:<div id="issues">Troubleshooting</div>

H3:Error: 'bax.bat' is not recognized
P:Make sure you are in the correct directory where bax.bat is located.

H3:Error: 'chmod' not recognized
P:This is a Linux command. On Windows, just run bax.bat directly.

H3:Error: 'public' folder not created
P:Run bax.bat or bax.sh to generate the output.

H3:Error: 'data' folder is empty
P:Add .zet files to the data/ folder before building.

H3:Error: 'config.zet' not found
P:Create config.zet in your project root.

